# CHANGELOG.md is append-only at the top — every PR adds a fresh "Unreleased"
# stanza. The standard 3-way merge fails almost every time because two PRs
# land their entries at the same line. The "union" merge driver concatenates
# both sides verbatim instead of conflicting; reviewers can re-order if needed.
#
# Open #6 from SECURITY_HANDOVER_2026-05-07.md. Saves ~30min of manual rebasing
# per multi-PR security batch (B1–B10 hit this 11 times in 24h).
#
# Note: `merge=union` is enabled here in the repo's .gitattributes; for the
# driver to take effect each developer's local git also needs no special
# config — `union` is built into git, no `git config merge.union.driver`
# line required.
CHANGELOG.md merge=union

# Shell scripts must keep LF line endings even on Windows checkouts. Otherwise
# git's `core.autocrlf=true` (the default on Windows installers) rewrites
# deploy.sh to CRLF, the +x bit drops, and the deploy fails on Linux as soon
# as the file is pushed. Pin the line ending explicitly.
*.sh text eol=lf
